				<p><p>I dont use NXC, so I am hesitant to propose this as an answer, but I will comment that the sensors ARE linear - not binary. They measure dark, grey, and light - On, middle, off of line. You simply devise a scheme to get a unique #, and use that as the SetPoint to PID - works great. See <a href="http://www.mindsensors.com/index.php?module=pagemaster&amp;PAGE_user_op=view_page&amp;PAGE_id=168" rel="nofollow">Mindsensors light array</a> for sample NXC code for their array. Adopt it to 3 sensors.</p>

<p>I don't know if this helps or not but is the scheme I use in RobotC; (higly shortened)</p>

